				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Malevolent wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I notice that damage currently caps at Bow damage + arrow damage. When does this change.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The formula doesn't really change ever, in as far as base damage goes (though it does take level into account), but you do get the following modifiers that can change it:
<br />

<br />
Level 50: If a mob is stationary but NOT rooted (i.e. if it is standing still, being tanked or snared and trying to run away) you get a Double Damage bonus (2x)
<br />

<br />
Level 55: You get Trueshot Discipline which gives you a 2.05x damage modifier
<br />

<br />
Then there's Archery Mastery AA's available at L59+
<br />

<br />
Go read this thread:
<br />

<br />
